I've never really been a podcast person bc how does someone find the time to listen to that many hour long podcasts or more?

30-60 sec clips are the end state of video content consumption as proven by tiktok, reels, clipping culture, etc

Subconsciously when someone says they listen to a lot of podcasts, I think that person must have a lot of free time and/or doesn't understand how to get that information more efficiently

Introducing $PROCOIN, the community-led governance token for Farcaster Pro users.

All 10k NFT holders are eligible for an airdrop.

But there’s a twist.

**The token will be untransferable until 500 Pro users claim.**

In order to get a mandate as a community token, we need broad support.

To claim, quotecast this post with the text “Ratifying @procoin governance”

All 10k NFT holders are eligible, but the first 500 claimers will receive ~5x the allocation.

Fascinating analysis on the first 10,000 pro subscribers. We knew the NFT was going to drive subscriptions, but this is some of the first analysis of how intense the farming was. 

24% of the people who minted had less than 10 followers.

Almost 12% had 0 followers. 

Speculation on the future value of the NFT is right here in black and white. 

There is no way someone with 0 followers paid to “support” the protocol or get the future benefits of longer casts and more photos.

Pro Subscribers should get to vote on the next like button

wrapped up a great call with some channel mods/owners

talked about possible roadmap for channels, what's missing, magic moments. some common threads:
- channels want more ways to drive engagement and growth, not just distribution. 
- discovery is important across apps, but so is having direct access to your community.
- folks run different types of channels, so flexibility matters across feeds, onboarding and moderation.
- the idea of owning your front page for your channel without relying on one app is powerful. 

thanks to those who still show up for channels!

Future of channels convo hosted by @cura is the don’t miss bi-weekly round table for me. Sooo good. @inceptionally @humpty.eth @anmworld3 @moe & of course @sahil all sharing thoughts & ideas 

Channels are in the BDFLs hands now. Which direction will they go? idk but follow cura & join the lobby. General consensus & working code.

Channels are miniapps
They should control signers
They issue entitlements 
They have wallets

FID based ‘mini’app centric

text: The only parasite that functionally replaces an organ. The tongue-eating louse (Cymothoa exigua) is one of the strangest and most disturbing parasites in the animal kingdom. It enters through the gills of a fish and attaches itself to the base of the tongue. It severs the blood vessels, causing the tongue to wither and fall off. Then it replaces the tongue, attaching itself to the stump and functioning like a prosthetic tongue. The fish can still eat and live normally—with the louse acting as its new tongue.
I regret asking for non crypto content on Farcaster

We're finally ready to unveil Epoch 8.

🥁🥁🥁 This epoch is an Ethereum-core alignment epoch. It's a special one because it's a major step in our broader roadmap to contribute to Ethereum's growth.

Like Epoch 7, there's no snapshot. Our internal reviewers will select projects based on impact and relevance.

Allocation window remains the same. ETH rewards are time-weighted and allocating to projects get you matched

🗓Application Deadline: 3 June, 2025 @ 11:59 pm PST

🛠 Who should apply?
Builders advancing Ethereum in 4 core areas:

1) Direct protocol improvements (consensus, execution, data availability, core networking)

2) Shared infrastructure (clients, testnets & tooling, p2p networking stacks, security & formal-verification frameworks, transparency)

3) Open dashboards, datasets, or studies (roll-ups, bridges, MEVs -  resulting insights must strengthen Ethereum)

4) Protocol-level research + specification work (advancing Ethereum's roadmap)

App link + eligibility criteria 👇

If you get caught using Amps on any submissions, you will likely get disqualified. 

We are trying to help the community find what matters, stop being greedy.
